      "message": "Yeah, good idea.  X-Macros are hard to read to begin with, and the lack of space and wrong indent aren\u0027t helping.\n\nI decided on a style and updated the file to be consistent.  It now is:\n\n#define THING_(x) \\    \u003c-- always a newline\n    case x: \\          \u003c-- matching indent of the file\n        do_thing()\n                       \u003c-- newline\n    THING_LIST         \u003c-- at indent level of the code above\n#undef THING_\n\nI may want to refine this more in the future, but I don\u0027t want to modify the code too heavily yet.  I\u0027m more of a fan of the X-Macro style that passes in the macro into the invocation, such as:\n\n#define MY_MACRO(x) ...\nTHING_LIST(MY_MACRO)\n#undef MY_MACRO",
